<body>

<div class="main-content">
    <header>
         Fire Disaster History
    </header>

    <p>
        Punjab has experienced multiple severe fire incidents over the years, including industrial fires, urban fires, and rural accidents. This page highlights key fire-related disasters and the steps taken by the state authorities to improve fire safety.
    </p>

    <h2>Fire Disaster Timeline</h2>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>1995 – Ludhiana Industrial Fire</h3>
        <p>
            • A major fire broke out in a textile factory in Ludhiana.<br>
            • Extensive damage to machinery and goods.<br>
            • Highlighted the need for better industrial fire safety regulations.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>2003 – Mandi Gobindgarh Chemical Fire</h3>
        <p>
            • Chemical warehouse caught fire, leading to evacuation of nearby residential areas.<br>
            • Prompted the establishment of chemical disaster response units under fire services.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>2011 – Amritsar Urban Fire</h3>
        <p>
            • Fire in a crowded market area led to property loss and minor casualties.<br>
            • Increased fire safety awareness in commercial areas.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>2018 – Ludhiana Factory Fire</h3>
        <p>
            • Fire erupted in a metal-processing unit.<br>
            • Firefighters contained the blaze within hours.<br>
            • Reinforced the need for emergency fire drills and inspections.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="year-block">
        <h3>2022 – Barnala Rural Fire</h3>
        <p>
            • Fire in a grain storage building caused major crop loss.<br>
            • Led to upgrades in rural fire response and training systems.
        </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
        Punjab’s fire disaster timeline demonstrates progress in fire safety preparedness, equipment modernization, and public awareness. With increased training and improved regulations, the state continues to enhance its ability to manage fire-related emergencies.
    </p>
</div>

